<document>
  <properties>
    <title>ECM Website Development</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="The JSP tag library">
      <subsection name="Importing the taglib">
        <p>The taglib definition file is present as <code>/META-INF/hst-template.tld</code> within the
          included HST jar file (see <a href="getting.html">getting the HST packages</a>) and
          should be found by your web server. The URI of the taglib is
          <code>http://www.hippoecm.org/jsp/hst-template</code> so to import the taglib in your jsp use the
          piece of code below. As prefix we recommend <code>hst-tmpl</code>, as a simple <code>h</code>
          is commonly used for jsf html tags.</p>
        <source><![CDATA[<%@taglib uri="http://www.hippoecm.org/jsp/hst-template" prefix="hst-tmpl"%>]]></source>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Tags">
        <p>The following tags are available:</p>
        <table cellpadding="3" cellspacing="0">
          <tr>
            <th>Tag</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/container-tag.html">&lt;hst-tmpl:container&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Used in template definition JSP file. It defines the containers/placeholders on the layout page.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/node-tag.html">&lt;hst-tmpl:node&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Exposes the current pageNode (selected document) to the JSP file.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/module-tag.html">&lt;hst-tmpl:module&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Uses the module definined in the className attribute of this tag to fetch content or execute some businesslogic.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/moduleParameter-tag.html">&lt;hst-tmpl:moduleParameter&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Uses the module definined in the className attribute of this tag to fetch content or execute some businesslogic.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><pre><a href="tag/link-tag.html">&lt;hst-tmpl:link&gt;</a></pre></td>
            <td>Creates a rewritten link for the current document, based on the urlmapping.</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
